    "title": "bitcoind and -server error message at the first start",
    "body": "When bitcoind (master) is started for the first time, it prints this:\n\nlinux-ku01:~/bitcoin/src # ./bitcoind\nError: To use the \"-server\" option, you must set a rpcpassword in the configuration file:\n\nI haven't used the -server option. It is set in bitcoind.cpp automatically:\n\nSoftSetBoolArg(\"-server\", true);\n\nThus the bitcoind/-server identification in rpcserver.cpp doesn't work as designed:\n\n```\n   string strWhatAmI = \"To use bitcoind\";\n    if (mapArgs.count(\"-server\"))\n        strWhatAmI = strprintf(_(\"To use the %s option\"), \"\\\"-server\\\"\");\n```\n",
